The paper discusses phishing and spear-phishing attacks and their detection techniques, which are primarily related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for detection, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses user awareness and education, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the need for real-time detection and performance evaluation metrics, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of feature extraction techniques, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
